KNAFEH. KANAFAH. KONIFA. KÜNEFE. Have you tried it yet??

I just had a rousing, long conversation about this dish and it got me obsessed all over again. This is me devouring a plate of it in Amman, Jordan, on the side of the road. It really is incredible how far this dish has traveled, and how special it is to so many different people and countries. Everyone tries to claim its origin. Everyone has a different way of making it. But literally everyone loves it. 

If you have never tried it, it’s a middle eastern dish of vermicelli or semolina dough, sandwiching gooey white cheese, baked or fried in butter, and doused with a rose water simple syrup. It’s utterly divine. Have you tried it?!? (Trader Joes’ version is a decent entry into knafeh but definitely not the best, you must try others!) 

#knafeh #kanafeh #künefe  #arabic #middleeasternfood #amman #jordan #foodjournalist

REPUBLIC OF CONGO 🇨🇬

Evan and I just came back from our first trip to Republic of Congo with @janegoodallinst, and I am floored by the conservation work being done there. I learned so much new information, including that the Jane Goodall Institute is way, way bigger picture than just chimpanzee conservation. Their work includes community building and enrichment, environmental conservation, and the conservation of many many other animal species. I’ll explain more in the following days! (The chimps in the video are being handed balls of rice as part of their daily food supplement, before being released fully back to the wild.) Something really important to note is JGI does not endorse handling or close proximity to wildlife. This represents a sanctuary context with trained professionals. 

Wildlife conservation in general can be very depressing, and I often walk away from our time in Africa feeling depressed and deflated, but I left Congo feeling very inspired. What Jane has put in motion is astounding. Sound up for the last slide - that was our soundtrack in the jungle!! Chimps all day long. 

More to come. 🇨🇬🐒

#africa #congo #republicofcongo #centralafrica #chimpanzee #wildlifeconservation #janegoodall
